Repetition (rhetorical device) - Repetition is the simple repeating of a word, within a sentence or a poetical line, with no particular placement of the words, in order to provide emphasis.
repetition definition: the act or an instance of repeating or being repeated.
"Repetition" (Information Society song) - "Repetition" is a 1989 ballad by Information Society.
Repetition (novel), a 1986 novel by the Austrian writer Peter Handke
"Repetition" (song), a song by David Bowie on his 1979 album Lodger
